{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778984659460,"sessionID":"ses_1cc48cd00fferg4IGHqG6hRtsQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Kr0nFgbXT4QoCw437OrbjCxM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:0061817` as requested and mapped it to `GO:0160214 endoplasmic reticulum-plasma membrane adaptor activity`.\n+\n+Validation passed locally.\n+\n+One follow-up point: direct annotations to `GO:0061817` are still present in AmiGO, with many remaining `IBA` annotations, so annotation migration/review should still be completed on the annotation side.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Obsoleted `GO:0061817 endoplasmic reticulum-plasma membrane tethering` because the issue correctly identified it as representing a molecular function rather than a biological process.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Converted `GO:0061817` to an obsolete term in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- Updated the label to `obsolete endoplasmic reticulum-plasma membrane tethering`\n+- Preserved the original definition provenance and converted the definition to the required `OBSOLETE.` form\n+- Removed the synonym and biological process parentage from the obsolete stanza\n+- Added an obsoletion comment explaining the reason\n+- Added `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31873\" xsd:anyURI`\n+- Added `is_obsolete: true`\n+- Added `replaced_by: GO:0160214` (`endoplasmic reticulum-plasma membrane adaptor activity`)\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The original BP term described membrane tethering accomplished by a tether/adaptor molecule, which is better modeled as the MF term `GO:0160214`.\n+- The issue discussion explicitly requested obsoletion and identified `GO:0160214` as the annotation target to use.\n+- `GO:0051643 endoplasmic reticulum localization` remains broader, but the direct replacement used here is the more specific MF requested in the issue comments.\n+\n+Validation and checks:\n+\n+- Checked the imported issue context and local repo guidance\n+- Used the term obsoletion workflow and edited the term through `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- Confirmed there were no internal GO ontology references to `GO:0061817` outside its own stanza\n+- Ran `make travis_build` in `src/ontology`; build passed\n+- Queried direct annotation usage with `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0061817`\n+\n+Annotation impact note:\n+\n+- Direct annotations to `GO:0061817` are still present in AmiGO, including many `IBA` annotations, so annotation migration remains necessary after the ontology obsoletion.\n+- This matches the issue history noting that annotation review/migration is part of the follow-up work.\n+\n+Checklist:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: analyzed issue context and intent\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: validated ontology state as part of local `make travis_build`\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: reviewed `GO:0061817`, `GO:0160214`, and `GO:0051643`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: not applicable beyond standard obsoletion pattern\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/checkin workflow via `terms/`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed obsolete-term logical/structural axioms\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: used obsoletion workflow\n+- [x] METADATA: added correct obsoletion metadata and issue tracker link\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: preserved existing definition provenance only; no new references introduced\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: committed local ontology change\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-g